## Assumptions
- **"All inline glass effects" means common patterns only** — The requirements said "all inline glass effects replaced," but many backdrop-blur usages are app-specific with unique opacity/color combinations (e.g., `backdrop-blur-xl bg-black/60` in alpha-wins). Assumed the intent was to standardize the *recurring* patterns, not force every single backdrop-blur into a utility.
- **App-specific animations are out of scope** — Brommie-quake has 15+ themed keyframes (earthquake shake, letter crumble, etc.) that are inherently non-reusable. Assumed these should remain app-local rather than being forced into shared utilities.
- **`glass-header` is a valid addition beyond the spec** — The requirements listed `glass`, `glass-sm`, `glass-strong` but didn't mention `glass-header`, `glass-input`, or `glass-overlay`. Assumed adding these was acceptable since the same inline patterns repeated across 15+ layout headers.
- **Shadow tokens should use CSS custom properties, not Tailwind theme extension** — The requirements said "theme shadow tokens" but didn't specify the mechanism. Chose CSS custom properties in `theme.css` (e.g., `--shadow-glass`) consumed via Tailwind's `shadow-[var(--shadow-glass)]` syntax.

## Decisions
- **Created `brommie-quake.css` as a dedicated app CSS file** rather than inlining styles or adding to globals — this app had 586 lines of highly specific animations that would pollute the shared theme.
- **Used `@utility` directive (Tailwind v4)** for glass utilities instead of `@apply`-based component classes — this keeps them composable as single-class utilities rather than locked into `@layer components`.
- **Added extra shadow tokens** beyond the three specified (`shadow-glass`, `shadow-glass-sm`, `shadow-glow`) — added `shadow-glass-hover`, `shadow-glass-hover-strong`, `shadow-glow-accent`, `shadow-glow-accent-sm`, `shadow-glow-accent-md`, and `shadow-lightbox` to cover the actual inline patterns found in the codebase.
- **Left ~191 inline patterns unconverted** — these are app-specific color shadows (e.g., `shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(255,255,255,0.8)]`) or Tailwind-native backdrop-blur classes that don't map cleanly to the standardized utilities.

## Items to Validate
- **Check `glass-header` appearance across all 15 app layouts** — the single utility replaces varied combinations of `bg-surface-bg/85`, `bg-background/80`, `border-white/10`, etc. Verify the unified look is acceptable for each app's visual identity.
- **Verify `glass-input` in proper-wine-pour form fields** — replaced 8 input styling instances; confirm the dark glass-input look (`bg-black/20`) works with the wine app's color scheme.
- **Review remaining inline shadows** — 10 shadow violations remain per the audit. Decide if any of these warrant new tokens or are acceptable as one-off values.
- **Confirm brommie-quake.css import** — this is a new CSS file that needs to be imported in the page component; verify it loads correctly in dev and production builds.